text: Dante Sealy (born April 17, 2003) is an American soccer player who plays as a forward for FC Dallas in Major League Soccer. ==Career== ===Club=== Dante Sealy plays for FC Dallas. He has played on loan with North Texas Soccer Club in USL League One. https://www.fcdallas.com/post/2019/02/26/fc-dallas- signs-25th-homegrown-player-dante- sealy#:~:text=FRISCO%20%E2%80%93%20FC%20Dallas%20has%20signed,any%20point%20in%20the%20future. ===International=== Sealy has featured for the USA u17 and u20 national teams in friendlies. https://www.fcdallas.com/post/2020/01/08/fc-dallas-homegrown- duo-called-u-20-national-team-camp ==Personal Life== He is the son of former FC Dallas player Scott Sealy. ==References== ==External links== * * * Dante Sealy at FC Dallas Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:American soccer players Category:African-American soccer players Category:American people of Trinidad and Tobago descent Category:Association football forwards Category:FC Dallas players Category:Homegrown Players (MLS) Category:North Texas SC players Category:People from Frisco, Texas Category:Soccer players from New York (state) Category:Soccer players from Texas Category:Sportspeople from Brooklyn Category:Sportspeople from the Dallas–Fort Worth metroplex Category:USL League One players
